SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
Financial control scenes demonstrate economic abuse as a power mechanism:
  1. Discovery — perpetrator finds evidence of spending or financial independence (receipt, bank app).
  2. Interrogation — demands justification for every expense; questions victim's right to money.
  3. Humiliation — belittles victim's earning capacity or contribution to the household.
  4. Prohibition — forbids victim from working, having their own bank account, or spending freely.
  5. Threat — threatens to cut off access to funds, kick them out, or expose alleged financial mismanagement.
The victim defends themselves, then shrinks under financial coercion.

